### Override Payload CMS Form Builder Field Configuration in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/plugins/form-builder.mdx

This example shows how to override an existing field, specifically the 'text' field, within the Payload CMS form builder plugin configuration. It merges the default properties with custom labels, allowing for tailored field presentation while retaining core functionality.

```ts
// payload.config.ts
formBuilderPlugin({
  // ...
  fields: {
    text: {
      ...fields.text,
      labels: {
        singular: 'Custom Text Field',
        plural: 'Custom Text Fields',
      },
    },
  },
})
```

