### Reuse Default Field Validations in Payload CMS (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/overview.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to combine custom validation logic with Payload CMS's built-in field validations. It shows calling a default validator (e.g., `text` for text fields) from within a custom `validate` function after applying specific custom checks. This allows extending, rather than entirely replacing, the default validation behavior.

```typescript
import { text } from 'payload/shared'

const field: Field = {
  name: 'notBad',
  type: 'text',
  validate: (val, args) => {
    if (val === 'bad') return 'This cannot be "bad"'
    return text(val, args)
  }
}
```

