### Register Custom Field Definition in Payload (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/PLUGIN-DEVELOPMENT.md

This TypeScript function, `CustomField`, defines a custom text field for Payload CMS. It specifies the field's `name`, `type`, and importantly, links its `admin.components.Field` property to the client-side `CustomFieldComponent` using an absolute path. It also allows for optional overrides to the field's configuration.

```typescript
// src/fields/CustomField/index.ts
import type { Field } from 'payload'

export const CustomField = (overrides?: Partial<Field>): Field => ({
  name: 'customField',
  type: 'text',
  admin: {
    components: {
      Field: '/fields/CustomField/Component#CustomFieldComponent',
    },
  },
  ...overrides,
})
```

